AGI -&nbsp;The French President, Emmanuel&nbsp;Macron, convened a European summit in Paris at the level of Heads of State and Government, in the light of what emerged at the Munich Security Conference on the theme of support for Ukraine. The Polish Foreign Minister Radosaw Sikorski said that the summit was scheduled for tomorrow. "It turns out to me that it is Monday," said the Foreign Minister, Antonio&nbsp;Tajani, asked by the chroniclers.
<br> "I am pleased that the Prime Minister, Donald Tusk, will go on Monday, at the invitation of President Emmanuel&nbsp; Macron&nbsp; to a meeting of European leaders. We must demonstrate our strength and unity," he wrote on X the Polish Foreign Minister, who initially mentioned as the date of the summit on Sunday, February 16, the day in which an informal meeting of foreign ministers will take place in Munich. As it turns out, the summit convened by&nbsp;Macron is still being defined. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
There is nothing yet defined. "There are discussions between European leaders on a possible informal meeting, but nothing has yet been defined," says Eliseo.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Media, Trump-Putin summit possible already at the end of month</h2>
A meeting in Saudi Arabia between US and Russia presidents, Donald Trump and Vladimir Putin, to discuss the conclusion of the conflict in Ukraine could take place by the end of the month. They told Reuters well informed sources, reports the Guardian. Next week, the sources, high officials from the United States and Russia will meet in the Arab country to prepare the ground for a possible summit.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Kellogg, currently separate talks with Kiev and Moscow
The United States is conducting a "double-track" approach with Russia and Ukraine and are having separate talks with Moscow and Kiev. The U.S. envoy Keith Kellogg says this during an event at the edge of the Monaco Conference. Kellogg said that both Ukraine and Europe must be part of the talks.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Kellogg, peace plan within days or weeks
A peace plan on the conflict in Ukraine could arrive "within a few days or weeks", said the US envoy. "You should give us some space and time, but when I say this, I don't talk about six months, but about days and weeks," he explained during a collateral event of the Conference. Kellogg said that Europe might not be physically present at the table of peace talks, but that European interests will be taken into account. &nbsp;
